&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10 PAs &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liverpool University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust are looking to appoint a Consultant in Acute Medicine to join the Acute Medical team based at the Aintree University Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is pivotal to the delivery and expansion of high quality care at Aintree and is a rare opportunity for an inspiring individual to be instrumental in shaping the future of our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Consultant in Acute Medicine, you will play a crucial role in ensuring the success of Acute Medicine which comprises an Ambulatory Emergency Care Unit and an Acute Medical Assessment Unit. The service model is strongly supported by the Trust and these appointments represent an on-going programme of expansion and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name; Paul Albert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title; Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address; paul.albert@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number; 01515295074&lt;/p&gt;
